In accordance with relevant Chinese laws, regulations, standards, and common practices in other countries and regions, we guarantee that you can exercise the following rights over your personal information. If you have questions or claims about the exercise of your rights, you can also contact us through [8. How to Contact Contact us via:
5.1. Right of Access
In principle, you can check your personal information through the following methods:
Account information: You can use My - Settings - in Butter Camera.
          Account and security, access or edit personal information in your account, change your password, perform account association or identity authentication, etc.
5.2. Right of corrections and additions
When you find that the personal information we process about you is incorrect or incomplete, you have the right to correct the error or incompleteness after verifying your identity and the correction does not affect the objectivity and accuracy of the information. If you want to make corrections or additions to incomplete information, you can use my -
        set up-
        Correct or supplement your personal data, or submit your request for correction or supplement to us through feedback and error reporting.
5.3. Right to erasure
You may make a request to us to delete your personal information under the following circumstances:
If we process your personal information in violation of laws, regulations or our agreement with you;
If our processing purposes have been fulfilled, cannot be fulfilled or are no longer necessary to fulfill the processing purposes;
If we stop providing products or services, or the retention period has expired;
If you withdraw your consent;
Other situations stipulated by laws and administrative regulations.
When you delete information from our services, we may not delete the corresponding information in the backup system immediately, but we will delete the information when the backup is updated. Please know and understand that if the retention period stipulated by laws, administrative regulations or described in this privacy agreement has not expired, or it is technically difficult to delete personal information, we will stop storing and taking necessary security protection measures. deal with.
5.4. Withdrawal of consent
Each business function requires some basic personal information to be completed. You can give or withdraw your consent at any time for the collection and use of additional personal information.
You can directly turn off system permissions such as camera, microphone, storage (also known as photo album), notifications, phone calls, change the scope of consent, or withdraw your authorization in the device system.
After you withdraw your consent, we will no longer be able to provide you with the services corresponding to your withdrawal of consent, and we will no longer use your corresponding personal information. However, your decision to withdraw your consent will not affect the previous processing of personal information based on your consent.
5.5. Right of cancellation
You can cancel your previously registered account.
You can log out of your account on Butter Camera via the following path: [My] - [Settings] - [Account and Security] - [Cancel Account].
When you are authorized to log in to Butter Camera through a third-party account (such as WeChat, Weibo, QQ, etc.), you need to apply to the third party to cancel your account.
5.6. Right of reproduction and portability
You have the right to copy the personal information we have collected about you. Under the conditions stipulated by laws and regulations, and in compliance with the instructions and conditions stipulated by the national cyberspace department, if technically feasible, you may also ask us to transfer your personal information to other entities designated by you.
5.7. The right to be notified in advance of the discontinuation of products and services.
Butter Camera is willing to accompany you all the time. If Butter Camera products cease operations due to special reasons, we will notify you within a reasonable period on the main page of the product or service or within the site, or by sending you an email or other appropriate method to reach you. You will stop collecting your personal information and will delete or anonymize your collected personal information in accordance with legal provisions.
5.8. Right to an explanation
You have the right to request an explanation of our personal information processing rules. You can contact us through the contact information in Section 8.
5.9 Display and control of personalized content and advertising
5.9.1. Display and control of personalized content
To facilitate you to control the personalized information you wish to receive, you can dynamically adjust your interests and preferences through the following paths, and we will push relevant personalized content to you based on your choices.
You can make adjustments at any time while browsing the content. If you don't like or are not interested in the recommended content displayed, you can click the "..." icon on the upper right side of the content to select "not interested" in the content. If you choose If you are "not interested" in this piece of content, we will reduce the recommendation of this type of content based on your choice. At the same time, we provide a reporting/feedback portal to listen to your opinions and suggestions.
Path:
[The "..." icon in the upper right corner of the content]-[Not interested]
[The "..." icon in the upper right corner of the content]-[Report/Feedback]
If you do not want us to push relevant personalized content to you based on your interest preferences, you can turn off "Receive Interest Recommendations" through [My] - [Settings] - [Privacy Settings]. When you choose to turn off "receive interest recommendations", you will not be able to enjoy personalized recommendation services. We will display content to you based on non-personalized factors such as popularity and content. You may see content that you are not interested in or even dislike, and your experience may be affected.
5.9.2. Display and control of personalized advertising
We may collect and use advertising identification information that complies with national or industry group standards. This identification is generated based on non-sensitive personal information such as device model and system configuration to provide you with more personalized information while protecting your privacy and service security. Programmatic advertising allows you to enjoy more convenient services. After we launch this function, we will also provide you with a shutdown function and inform you of the shutdown path. If you do not want us to use advertising identification information for the above purposes, you can choose to shut it down at any time. After closing, we will no longer obtain and process the Internet advertising identifier.
If you don't like or are not interested in the programmatic ads pushed to you, you can close the ad at any time by clicking the "×" icon on the lower right side of the ad, or you can choose to be "not interested" in the ad. If you choose "not interested" in this advertisement, the personalized recommendation strategy will be adjusted based on your feedback. At the same time, a reporting/feedback portal is provided to listen to your opinions and suggestions.
Path:
[The "×" icon at the bottom right of the advertisement]-[Reason for selection]-[Confirm]
[The "×" icon at the bottom right of the advertisement]-[Not interested]
[The "×" icon at the bottom right of the advertisement]-[Report/Feedback]
Programmatic advertising is one of the universal advertising technologies that makes intelligent recommendations based on your preferences within third-party applications. Butter Camera only provides programmatic advertising docking technology and will not obtain your behavior or personal data within third-party applications. You can choose to turn on or off this technology by turning on/off the [My]-[Settings]-[Privacy Settings]-[Programmatic Advertising Recommendation] switch. If you turn off the switch, the number of ads you see will not be reduced, but Advertising will be less precise.
5.10. Exceptions to the exercise of rights
We may not be able to respond to your requests for access, correction and addition, deletion, copying and portability, information, and decision-making under the following circumstances:
Directly related to national security and national defense security;
Directly related to public safety, public health, and major public interests;
Directly related to criminal investigation, prosecution, trial and execution of judgments;
We have sufficient evidence to show that you have subjective malice or abused your rights (for example, your request will endanger public safety and the legitimate rights and interests of others, or your request exceeds the scope that can be covered by general technical means and commercial costs);
Responding to the request of the personal information subject will cause serious damage to the legitimate rights and interests of you or other individuals or organizations;
Involving trade secrets;
Situations otherwise stipulated by laws and administrative regulations.
5.11. How to respond to your rights request
For security reasons, you may be required to provide a written request or otherwise prove your identity.
We may ask you to verify your identity before processing your request. After verification, we will respond within fifteen working days. You can contact us by sending an email to hello@bybutter.com.
In principle, we do not charge fees for your reasonable requests.
However, for repeated requests that exceed reasonable limits, we will charge a certain cost depending on the circumstances. For those that are gratuitously repetitive, require excessive technical means (for example, require the development of new systems or fundamentally change existing practices), pose risks to the legitimate rights and interests of others, or are very impractical (for example, involving information stored on backup tapes) request, we may deny it.
6. How we handle minors’ personal information
Muke Company attaches great importance to the protection of minors’ information.
Our products and services are primarily intended for adults. We will only process the personal information of minors as permitted by laws and regulations and with the consent of parents or other guardians.
If you are a minor under the age of 14, before using Butter Camera products and services, you should ask your parents or other guardians to read this privacy carefully, or you should ask your parents or other guardians to read this privacy policy carefully together under the supervision and guidance of your parents or other guardians. Agreement, and
with the consent of your parent or other guardian to use our products and services or provide information to us.
If we discover that we have collected personal information from minors under the age of 14 without first obtaining verifiable parental or other guardian consent, we will take steps to delete the relevant information as soon as possible. If at any time a guardian has reason to believe that we have collected a minor's personal information without the guardian's consent, you may send the relevant information to hello@bybutter.com.
7. Revision of Privacy Agreement
Our Privacy Policy is subject to change.
We will not reduce your rights under this Privacy Agreement without your explicit consent. We will post any changes to this Privacy Agreement on this page.
For major changes, we will notify you on the main exposure page of the product or service, an in-site letter, or send you an email or other appropriate method to reach you.
If you do not agree to these changes, please stop using Butter Camera products and services immediately.
Major changes referred to in this agreement include but are not limited to:
Significant changes to our service model. Such as the purpose of processing personal information, types of personal information processed, how personal information is used, etc.;
We have undergone significant changes in ownership structure, organizational structure, etc. Such as changes in owners caused by business adjustments, bankruptcy mergers, etc.;
The main objects to whom personal information is provided, transferred or publicly disclosed change;
Significant changes in your rights to participate in the processing of personal information and how to exercise them;
When our responsible department, contact information and complaint channels for handling personal information security change;
When the personal information security impact assessment report indicates that there is a high risk.
If there are any matters not covered in this privacy agreement, the "Baidu Privacy Protection Statement" shall prevail.
